---
import CaseStudy from "@/layouts/case-study.astro"
import { getProject } from "@/data/projects"

const project = getProject("ncga-template-system")!
---

<CaseStudy
  project={project}
  title="NCGA Reusable Template System"
  description="A draft case study about reusable templates and visual standards for recurring public-sector communications."
>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    This page is a placeholder for a future case study about template systems
    and production standards at the North Carolina General Assembly. The current
    framing comes from my resume: reusable templates, consistent recurring
    materials, and complex legislative content made easier to scan and produce
    accurately.
  </p>

  <h2>Problem</h2>
  <!-- TODO: Add the recurring material types, production pain points, accessibility considerations, and stakeholder context. -->
  <p>
    Recurring legislative materials needed a more consistent structure so teams
    could produce accurate print and digital communications without rebuilding
    the same decisions each cycle.
  </p>

  <h2>Role</h2>
  <p>
    Graphic and production designer at the North Carolina General Assembly,
    working across layout systems, visual standards, production workflows, and
    public-sector communication needs.
  </p>

  <h2>Next Draft Pass</h2>
  <!-- TODO: Add representative artifacts, template anatomy, accessibility notes, and a real outcome grounded in production workflow. -->
  <p>
    The next pass should add representative artifacts, define the template
    system’s parts, and describe production improvements with only verifiable
    claims.
  </p>
</CaseStudy>
